'''Royd Allan Reuel Tolkien''' (born [[16 July]] [[1969]]) is a great-grandson of [[J.R.R. Tolkien]], the grandchild of Tolkien's second son, [[Michael Tolkien|Michael]]. His birthname is Royd Baker, but he changed his name to Royd Tolkien when he became adult .{{fact}}

Royd Tolkien played a [[Rangers of Ithilien|Ranger]] in ''[[The Lord of the Rings: The Return of the King]]''<ref>{{webcite|author=Emma Dibdin|articleurl=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/movies/interviews/a438695/the-hobbit-qa-with-royd-tolkien.html|articlename='The Hobbit': Q&A with Royd Tolkien|dated=19 November 2012|website=[http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/ digitalspy.co.uk]|accessed=25 October 2014}}</ref> and the [[Rangers of Ithilien|burier]] of the [[Witch-king]] in the Extended Edition of ''[[The Hobbit: The Desolation of Smaug]]''.<ref>{{webcite|author=|articleurl=http://www.theonering.net/torwp/2014/10/24/93443-royd-tolkiens-cameo-spotted-in-desolation-of-smaug-extended-edition/|articlename=Royd Tolkienâ€™s cameo spotted in Desolation of Smaug Extended Edition|dated=24 October 2014|website=TORN|accessed=25 October 2014}}</ref>

He has stated that he doesn't know whether or not he ever met his great-grandfather but his sister, Amanda is was a year older, does have a photo with him. He owns a signed copy of ''[[The Hobbit]]'', with the inscription "To Royd, JRR Tolkien".<ref>{{webcite|author=Christopher Hooton, Lesley O Toole|articleurl=https://metro.co.uk/2012/12/12/royd-tolkien-i-was-welcomed-with-open-arms-on-hobbit-set-3312366/|articlename=Royd Tolkien: I was welcomed with open arms on Hobbit set|dated=12 December 2012|website=[https://metro.co.uk/ Metro]|accessed=29 April 2025}}</ref> 

